parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window regulators can cause the windows to become stuck or inoperable, which can lead to safety risks, such as being unable to roll up windows in an emergency situation.
symptoms: Windows won't roll up or down
grinding or sand-on-glass sounds when rolling windows
windows stuck in up or down position
windows require manual assistance to roll up or down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear windshield washer can cause reduced visibility while driving, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Rear windshield washer does not work or only works intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel sending unit can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while in motion, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the fuel gauge does not accurately display the fuel level
and the fuel pump may need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank valve can cause fuel to overflow when filling, leading to a fire hazard and potential accidents.
symptoms: the fuel pump does not shut off automatically
and the fuel gauge may not accurately display the fuel level.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel sending unit can cause the fuel pump to malfunction, leading to engine stalling, difficulty starting, or even a fire hazard, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the fuel pump does not turn on
the fuel sending unit has a hole or corrosion
the electrical connection is melted or corroded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical fires can cause damage to the vehicle, injuries, or even fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke or fire from the engine compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of instrument gauges can cause safety issues, as drivers may not be aware of critical vehicle information, such as speed or fuel level.
symptoms: and fuel gauges malfunction or go to zero
gauges return to normal after the vehicle has been parked and cooled down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of window regulators can cause safety issues, as windows may become stuck or fall, causing injuries or distractions while driving.
